---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Contact — LrGeniusAI" description="Get help, report bugs, or share ideas for LrGeniusAI — the free open-source AI workflow suite for Lightroom Classic.">

  <section class="contact-hero">
    <h1>Get in Touch</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">LrGeniusAI is an open-source project — community happens on GitHub. Pick the right channel below and we'll get back to you as quickly as we can.</p>
  </section>

  <div class="contact-grid">

    <a class="contact-card" href="https://github.com/LrGenius/LrGeniusAI/issues/new/choose" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
      <div class="card-icon">🐛</div>
      <h2>Bug Report</h2>
      <p>Something not working as expected? Open a GitHub Issue and describe what happened, what you expected, and which OS / AI provider you're using.</p>
      <span class="card-link">Open an Issue →</span>
    </a>

    <a class="contact-card" href="https://github.com/LrGenius/LrGeniusAI/discussions/new/choose" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
      <div class="card-icon">💬</div>
      <h2>Questions &amp; Ideas</h2>
      <p>Have a question about setup, a feature request, or just want to share how you use LrGeniusAI? Start a GitHub Discussion — no account needed to read, just to post.</p>
      <span class="card-link">Start a Discussion →</span>
    </a>

    <a class="contact-card" href="https://github.com/LrGenius/LrGeniusAI" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
      <div class="card-icon">⭐</div>
      <h2>Star &amp; Contribute</h2>
      <p>LrGeniusAI is free and open-source (AGPL-3.0). If it saves you time, a GitHub star goes a long way. Pull requests, translations and docs improvements are very welcome.</p>
      <span class="card-link">View on GitHub →</span>
    </a>

    <a class="contact-card" href="https://github.com/LrGenius/LrGeniusAI/wiki/Getting-Started" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
      <div class="card-icon">📖</div>
      <h2>Documentation</h2>
      <p>Before opening an issue, check the wiki — installation, Ollama / LM Studio setup, and the plugin guide are all there and kept up to date with each release.</p>
      <span class="card-link">Read the Docs →</span>
    </a>

  </div>


</Layout>

<style>
  .contact-hero {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 3.5rem 0 2rem;
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .contact-hero h1 {
    font-size: 2.2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .subtitle {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: #555;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .contact-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 2.5rem;
  }
  .contact-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    padding: 1.75rem;
    border: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
    border-radius: 12px;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    transition: box-shadow 0.25s ease, border-color 0.25s ease, transform 0.2s ease;
    background: #fff;
  }
  .contact-card:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 6px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.09);
    border-color: var(--color-primary, #0066cc);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }
  .card-icon {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1;
  }
  .contact-card h2 {
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--color-primary, #0066cc);
  }
  .contact-card p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: #444;
    line-height: 1.65;
    flex: 1;
    margin: 0 0 1.1rem;
  }
  .card-link {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-primary, #0066cc);
  }
  .note {
    background: #f7f7f9;
    border: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #555;
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 auto 3rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
</style>
